<TEXT>
most of the psychological tests now in use do a 
poor job of evaluating black personality and attitudes according 
to a black psychologist who says he has developed a test to remedy 
the problem 
it is time we begin to show sensitivity to black american 
culture and stop trying to make black americans conform to anglo 
test material and test biases said robert l williams a 
professor of psychology and black studies at washington university 
in st louis 
williams made the comments saturday to about 150 people at a 
psychology conference where participants studied the impact of 
ethnicity and race on their clients 
black lifestyles should be examined and understood in terms of 
their historical cultural and social realities and not in terms of 
a comparison with the experiences of other groups for example 
euroamericans said williams 
he said he has developed a standardized test for blacks called 
themes concerning blacks 
the test now being used by a number of schools corporations 
and psychologists consists of 20 charcoal drawings depicting 
various aspects of black culture and lifestyles in rural and urban 
areas he said 
culturally specific tests are necessary because people of 
various ethnic backgrounds may perform badly on tests designed for 
and by euroamericans and they may be labeled inaccurately as a 
result williams said 
mislabeling may have profoundly negative effects on 
intellectual and personality development williams said 
he said he was told by a white counselor in elementary school 
that he had only borderline intelligence and should take manual 
training programs in high school williams later went to college 
and earned a doctorate from washington university 
the conference which ended saturday was sponsored by the 
chicago school of professional psychology 
</TEXT>
