<TEXT>
m butterfly which opened sunday night is 
a brilliant new play with layers of ironies fantasies sexual and 
romantic ambiguities and gender reversals by individuals and even 
the occident and the orient 
the play californiaborn playwright david henry hwangs 
broadway debut stars john lithgow and bd wong both giving 
striking performances 
the story turns on its head puccinis opera madame 
butterfly in which navy lt pinkerton marries madame butterfly 
while stationed in japan then sails away while she lovingly 
believes hell come back 
in m butterfly meaning monsieur butterfly it is the 
foreign man posted in the orient who deeply loves lithgow plays 
rene gallimard attached to the french embassy in beijing in 1960 
the naive babyfaced gallimard who narrates the story in 
flashback from a french prison sees the woman of his dreams song 
liling bd wong singing madama butterfly he calls the 
singer butterfly ever after 
but butterfly is a chinese actor playing a woman and whether 
butterfly cares for gallimard is unknown they have an affair for 
20 years in which gallimard never sees butterfly naked or allows 
himself to realize butterfly is a man 
hwang whose plays have been acclaimed offbroadway was 
inspired by reallife reports of a similar situation in an 
espionage trial in france 
in m butterfly butterfly is a communist agent who gives 
gallimard misinformation to pass on to america about vietnam 
eventually butterfly gets him to become a courier and photograph 
documents 
at gallimards treason trial butterfly in a business suit 
tells the judge the west has a racial mentality about the east 
the west thinks of itself as masculine the east as delicate 
wanting to be submissive 
the play is talky as plays of ideas are but lithgows 
character as written and acted is a rich one gallimard had a 
wife rose gregorio and a fling with a young blonde lindsay 
frost whose frank speech he considered masculine butterfly asked 
by the judge george n martin how gallimard could not know he was 
a man says men believe what they want to believe 
the play is ambiguous about whether gallimard wanted to believe 
in his dream woman or whether he was without knowing his own 
secret homosexual the two argue about that for too long after 
the trial gallimard insisting i am a man who loved a woman 
created by a man 
the play ends like the opera with gallimard having taken over 
butterflys situation and finally her role 
director john dexter has seamlessly woven eastern and western 
stage elements stagehands wearing black so theyre unseen as 
in oriental theater move furniture and props the stage has a red 
backdrop and a black platform encircled by a sweeping white ramp 
that reaches high into the wings 
in other reviews the daily news howard kissel said the play is 
witty and filled with provocative images but baffling 
offbroadway its assets would be properly appreciated the 
review said here its slick trappings set expectations it cannot 
meet 
reviewer frank rich of the new york times said the singular 
play treats a number of universal conflicts men versus women and 
east versus west 
though m butterfly presents us with a visionary work that 
bridges the history and culture of two worlds the production stops 
crushingly short of finding the gripping human drama that merges 
mr hwangs story with his brilliant play of ideas the critic 
wrote 
