the irish republican army shot 
dead a policeman today two days after a mob at an ira funeral 
killed two british soldiers 
police said the policeman was shot in the head in a jeep in the 
roman catholic creggan district of londonderry and died at a 
hospital 
the ira claimed responsibility in a clandestine message to 
belfast media 
the officer whose name was not made public immediately was the 
23rd person and the second policeman to die in the british province 
this year 
police sources said today about 30 suspects were being sought in 
connection with the mob attack saturday on two british soldiers 
the outlawed ira also claimed responsiblity for the killings of the 
soldiers 
irish and british newspapers said a police roundup of suspects 
in catholic strongholds in belfast was imminent 
police made no formal statement but the sources requesting 
anonymity said suspects were identified by studying videotape of 
saturdays rampage in which the two soldiers were beatend and 
stripped naked by the crowd and shot by ira gunmen 
three suspects were arrested immediately after the killings 
in the catholic markets district of west belfast police seized 
600 pounds of explosive material early today and said they 
arrested a woman 
in london northern ireland secretary tom king announced today 
an immediate review of its new policy of not policing irish 
republican army funerals following the killings saturday 
in all five people died during burials or funeral corteges in a 
