congress should order american troops and 
military installations pulled out of japan unless the japanese do 
much more to pay for western defense sen ted stevens said monday 
stevens said that because of the strength of the japanese 
economy and its favorable trade balance with the unite states 
tokyo should be able to foot the bill for its own defense 
the yen has conquered a great portion of american the 
alaska republican told a group of pentagon officials during a 
hearing of the senate appropriations military construction 
subcommittee now that the japanese economy is going full tilt 
japan should pay the full cost of keeping us troops and 
facilities in that nation stevens said 
stevens said he was putting the pentagon on notice that he 
plans to offer a bill next year that would require us military 
withdrawals from japan 
stevens said his proposal would be similar to legislation which 
was routinely sponsored and just as routinely defeated by 
former sen mike mansfield dmont calling for us troops to be 
withdrawn from europe mansfield is now us ambassador to japan 
mansfield was right stevens said 
the united states has been pressuring japan to increase defense 
spending and take more responsibility for its defense those calls 
have been particularly loud on capitol hill where japan has come 
under increasing criticism for its trade policies 
in tokyo prime minister noboru takeshita said monday that 
japans military power should match its economic strength 
japan last year formally scrapped a decadeold ceiling which 
limited defense spending to 1 percent of its gross national 
product during the current 198690 defense buildup plan the 
government says japans defense spending will total 11987 billion 
japan pays about 40 percent of the 59 billion cost of 
maintaining us facilities in the country 
richard armitage assistant secretary of defense for 
international security affairs told stevens that congress 
shouldnt engage in japanbashing 
japan is increasing its defense budget armitage said and the 
spending total is on the verge of passing the british french 
and west german defense budgets 
we should look beyond the popular allybashing rhetoric of a 
campaign year armitage said 
stevens responded that he would have offered his proposal this 
year but it shouldnt be an electionyear issue 
japan is now meeting all its mutually agreed defense goals 
armitage said and is building up its naval fleet 
