police arrested 34 taxi drivers monday for 
violating antipollution rules that ban half of the capitals 
15000 taxis from the city center each day 
a spokesman for the cabbies said they intentionally entered the 
district to challenge the ban which they dismiss as illegal 
the ban is part of a set of wideranging restrictions limiting 
traffic in athens the measures are aimed at dispelling an 
eyestinging brown smog that hangs over the city in calm weather 
the taxi drivers were arrested because they brought cabs with 
even licenseplate numbers into the 5squaremile central zone on a 
day reserved for oddnumbered vehicles said a spokesmen for the 
traffic police 
nikos stekas a spokesman for the athens taxi drivers union 
said cabbies will defy the ban every day claiming it cuts their 
income in half 
the taxi drivers face a oneyear jail term or a 370 fine 
police said they could also lose their operating permits for a 
month 
