<DOCNO> AP880321-0162 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
here are some of the recommendations made 
monday by the commission on education of the deaf in a 
congressionally ordered report 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the us department of education should put less emphasis on 
placing deaf students in the least restrictive environment and 
more on providing an appropriate education for many that means 
special schools and centers for the deaf 
the department should specify that removing a deaf child from a 
regular classroom does not require compelling evidence 
congress should grant full recognition to american sign 
language as a native language just like spanish under the 
bilingual education act and programs 
more help and services for lowachieving deaf students not 
just the college bound 
congress should require the federal communications commission 
to force broadcasters to caption their programming and consider 
the same requirement for film producers 
congress should caption its own televised proceedings 
congress should require the fcc to issue rules making new tv 
sets capable of decoding closed captions until such sets become 
widely available decoders should be distributed free to the deaf 
earlier identification of deaf infants it isnt necessary to 
test the hearing of every newborn just those at high risk of 
hearing impairments 
the us department of health and human services should issue 
guidelines to help states improve screening procedures 
parents should have the option to choose what type of school 
their child attends and must believe in whichever communication 
method is chosen for their childs educational program 
congress should pass a quality in deaf education bill 
changes should be made in the management of gallaudet 
university including appointment of a majority of deaf people to 
its board of trustees 
congress should bar hearing undergraduates from gallaudet 
which in 1985 began to admit a handful interested in careers in 
education of the deaf 
the model secondary school for the deaf at gallaudet should 
admit more lowachieving deaf students so that it more closely 
mirrors the national demographics of secondary schoolage deaf 
children 
the government should expand its regional postsecondary 
education program to the southwest it now has programs in other 
regions 
congress should establish a national center on deafness 
research at gallaudet 
congress should create a national institute on deafness and 
other communication disorders at the national institutes of health 
gallaudet and the national technical institute for the deaf in 
rochester ny should limit enrollment of foreign students to 10 
percent and charge them 75 percent of the actual costs or about 
18250 a year 
both gallaudet and ntid should do a better job of hiring the 
deaf only 12 percent of the staff at ntid and 25 percent at 
gallaudet are deaf 
</TEXT>
