necessary to protect the plo mission and provide alternative 
accommodations to its members on un international territory 
the 1987 antiterrorist act passed by congress went into effect 
monday it requires the government to close the plo mission whose 
offices are in a townhouse in new york city 
zehdi labib terzi the plos permanent representative to the 
un said he would not voluntarily close the 13yearold mission 
near park avenue as ordered by attorney general edwin meese iii 
