who were filmed surrounding and beating the soldiers unmarked car 
with iron bars and dragging them out had gone into hiding 
a massive murder investigation is under way in which all 
possible resources are involved to identify all those 
responsible king said of the manhunt in west belfast 
three people were arrested saturday and police sources said 
monday that up to 30 others were being sought after hours of 
scrutiny of film taken by an army helicopter which hovered over the 
scene and by tv networks gruesome scenes of the attack also were 
shown on television 
cpls derek wood and david howes in plainclothes were 
surrounded when they drove up to the cortege dragged from their 
car stripped beaten and shot dead 
king said an emergency meeting of senior government ministers 
from britain and the republic of ireland will be held this week to 
consider stepped up security 
king denied charges by northern ireland protestant politicians 
that police and troops failed to come to the soldiers aid because 
of political orders to stay away from ira funerals 
he said it was not immediately clear to police watching film 
relayed from the helicopter that soldiers were under attack because 
police were certain there were no security forces in the area 
whatsoever 
he said the soldiers were under general orders to keep out of 
catholic districts unless on operational duty and had no reason 
to be in the vicinity of the funerals he said he did not know 
why they were there 
as the commons listened in silence king praised the corporals 
identified as signals corpsmen heading back to barracks after doing 
maintenance work at a base in belfast for their restraint in 
firing only one shot into the mob that surrounded them 
the truth is that there will be new depths of horror again 
as long as this awful and evil campaign of terrorism and revenge 
continues king said 
it has got to stop in the name of humanity and if there is to 
be any decent future for the people of northern ireland and for all 
those living in the island of ireland and if the evil shroud of 
terrorism is to be lifted from the united kingdom as whole 
since 1969 2638 people have been killed in the sectarian 
violence in this protestantdominated province the ira is fighting 
to end british rule and unite northern ireland with the catholic 
republic of ireland under a leftist administration 
