<TEXT>
warning that louisiana is in a 
terrifying financial crisis gov buddy roemer on monday told 
the legislature that he must have unprecedented authority to make 
budget cuts in order to keep the state afloat 
we must build on the foundation of a balanced budget roemer 
said in his address before lawmakers called into special session 
although the governor said the first step would be to cut 
spending he said tax increases would be necessary later 
roemer said the state faces a more than 2 billion problem 
including a 210 million cashflow shortage that could shut down 
government within 50 days a projected 756 million deficit for the 
198889 fiscal year and an accumulated debt of 13 billion 
we inherited a mess a real unbelievable mess the governor 
said 
roemer asked lawmakers to give him the authority to cut up to 20 
percent from each department and eliminate entire state programs 
through the rest of the fiscal year ending june 30 
i must have the power to make decisions and accelerate the 
decisionmaking process he said 
the governor said that if thengov edwin edwards had accepted 
100 million in budget cuts that roemer proposed during the 
transition the cashflow problem would have been averted 
time is eating us alive he said 
roemer said the legislature could reverse any budget decisions 
he makes when lawmakers convene for their regular session in april 
adding i am not requesting that you abdicate your responsibility 
in the budget process 
the special session would center around solving the shortterm 
cash problem and laying the groundwork for paying off the 
accumulated debt budget cuts made now will translate into savings 
in the next fiscal year he said 
as part of a government reorganization plan to save money 
roemer asked lawmakers to divide the department of health and human 
resources into two agencies eliminate the department of urban and 
community affairs and forgive loans taken from dedicated or 
specialuse funds to keep the state operating 
besides eliminating the entire urban affairs department which 
would require separate legislative action roemer did not cite 
specifically what state programs he wanted to eliminate but he 
said some state institutions may have to be closed 
tax increases and borrowing alone without budget cuts will not 
solve the financial problem and will hamper efforts to attract new 
business and industry to louisiana roemer warned 
more borrowing or new taxes are not now the answer he said 
we will need to do both eventually but each action must be 
carefully thought out and precisely planned 
roemer said his administration already had taken steps to save 
214 million through such steps as better utilization of state 
office space reducing the number of state vehicles by a third 
limiting bond issues for major construction projects and the 
elimination of positions held by political appointees 
the regular legislative session will concern itself with plans 
to pay off the longterm debt an overhaul of the states tax 
system a balanced budget for 198788 education and environmental 
changes and a plan to diversify the states economy roemer said 
the ability to attract new business to louisiana will depend 
upon our willingness to make tough decisions the governor said 
i did not expect nor did i ask for this perilous economic 
situation but i am prepared to lead us through these tough times 
in such a way that we protect essential services and we avoid 
having to make these choices over and over and over again it will 
not be easy he said 
after the house and senate convened shortly after 5 pm 
administrationbacked bills aimed at slashing state spending and 
reorganizing government were introduced in both chambers 
in the house legislation was put forth to give roemer the 
temporary authority he wants to cut spending 
