of whom have equipment from earlier climbs and a cash payment is 
usually negotiated in lieu of equipment 
the daily salary in the scheme of things is peanuts said 
langley 
he said the pay to the government liaison officer for example 
is 2 a day his equipment allowance comes to the equivalent of 
800 
other expenses include 1000 for an agency to help ease the way 
through the nepalese bureaucracy 350 for required insurance for 
climbers and sherpas and the cost of getting climbers and their 
equipment to nepal 
