liliane montevecchi is a french singerdancer 
whose cabaret show on the boulevard opened in february and 
keeps getting extended at the tiny offbroadway kaufman theater 
whether she will let it extend into the summer she cant say 
i dont make plans i do whatever pleases me 
im like a cork on the ocean and just let it ride she says 
in french accented english her words punctuated by a hearty laugh 
her father was italian her mother french she grew up in paris 
she was the star of the folies bergere for 10 years minus the 
feathers of the folies shes doing her first onewoman show 
in on the boulevard she wears a black longsleeved 
miniskirted dress accenting her gamine face svelte figure and 
shapely legs after intermission for a boulevard stroll she 
belts on a very frenchlooking trench coat she bought it for 25 
in a salvation army store near the manhattan apartment where shes 
