<TEXT>
claire molloy sits in her 
wheelchair mulling the possible purchase of a knit jogging suit 
that just happens to be in lilac currently her favorite color 
what i really need are lilac sneakers said the 65yearold 
resident of the bartley manor nursing home before tossing the 
jogging suit back on the rack 
she and other residents were choosing their spring wardrobes 
over coffee and doughnuts in the nursing homes sunny recreation 
room 
the athome shopping service is made available by silverthreads 
inc an audubon njbased company that specializes in 
healthcare apparel 
silverthreads actually is a traveling store that sets up shop in 
nursing homes in delaware maryland new jersey pennsylvania 
virginia and west virginia its mailorder catalog serves other 
customers many of whom are cared for at home by their families 
silverthreads president martin misiaszek who started the firm 
10 years ago said the company tries to provide its elderly 
customers with everyday apparel such as nightgowns and dresses as 
well as specialized apparel such as washable shoes for patients who 
may be incontinent 
what we try to do is bring a clothing store to a nursing 
home said misiaszek who has a degree in healthcare management 
silverthreads treats its customers most of whom are over 85 
years old with respect and understanding he said 
we all like to see what were going to purchase whether it 
has two pockets or a belt these people are no different he said 
while on the road silverthreads packs its inventory racks 
bins and mirrors in a 20foot truck its driven by misiaszeks 
younger brother bob the companys vice president 
silverthreads most popular lines are shirts dresses and night 
clothes that close in the back and mens pants with snaps on the 
sides he said 
these are for people who cant dress themselves so nurses can 
dress them bob misiaszek said its a big help for nurses 
aides 
other speciality items include terrycloth bibs with velcro 
snaps flannel and corduroy lap wraps that tie around a wheelchair 
patients waist and cushy nonskid slippers for patients with foot 
disorders 
we try to have clothes that allow people to retain their 
selfesteem bob misiaszek said while straightening a bin filled 
with dainty womens underwear and frilly nightgowns 
prices are range from 24 for cotton dresses with front zippers 
to 16 for a twopiece jumpsuit 
the prices are reasonable weve been looking around and the 
prices here are better than a department store said jerry 
