<TEXT>
investment in plant and equipment by us 
business is likely to increase about 88 percent this year but only 
05 percent in 1989 according to a survey released monday 
manufacturers are likely to lead the way this year with a 125 
percent increase in investment but trail in 1989 with a 29 
percent decrease data resources inc of lexington mass said 
the larger nonmanufacturing sector is expected to be more 
stable with a 66 percent increase this year and a 27 percent 
increase in 1989 the survey said based on answers from 457 
companies 
companies were more optimistic about 1988 than in a previous 
survey conducted just before the october stock market crash when 
they predicted overall investment in plant and equipment would rise 
62 percent according to data resources a unit of mcgrawhill inc 
many economists say the stock market crash cooled off the 
economy at a time when it was in danger of overheating and falling 
into recession some are now pushing back the date of an expected 
recession to 1989 
