reporters after the threehour session 
the francogerman economic council was established in january as 
a way of better coordinating policy between the two neighboring 
nations 
the council is to meet four times a year and comprise the 
nations finance and economics ministers and the heads of the two 
central banks 
west germanys central bank president karl otto poehl is known 
to have been skeptical about the council because of fears that it 
may infringe upon his bundesbanks independence 
