batus inc took its campaign for farmers 
group inc to the companys shareholders monday soliciting proxies 
to support reconsideration of its bid for one of the nations 
largest insurers 
batus said the nonbinding resolution will be introduced at 
farmers annual stockholders meeting may 20 at the companys los 
angeles headquarters 
on march 10 farmers board unanimously rejected a hostile 
takeover offer of 63 a share or 44 billion and called upon its 
shareholders to do the same the offer was described as being 
substantially less than the company is worth 
the board which has refused to enter into negotiations also 
announced it was exploring a variety of alternatives to the batus 
bid including restructuring or consolidating with another company 
farmers said it has had discussions with an unidentified third 
party about a possible leveraged buyout to counter the offer from 
batus the us subsidiary of british bat industries plc 
farmers group shares fell to 6250 down 112 in active 
overthecounter trading monday 
in seeking the proxies batus said its resolution would give 
stockholders an opportunity to express their support for the 
merger at no less than 63 a share and would encourage the 
directors to pursue such a sale 
in case a higher bidder emerged the resolution recommends that 
farmers directors consider in good faith whether to negotiate 
with such a bidder 
batus latest maneuver was no surprise said tom welch 
director of corporate investments for farmers we have been 
expecting it he declined further comment 
batus spokesman wilson wyatt jr said the solicitation was being 
handled by the carter organization in new york 
wyatt also said batus does not intend to oppose or take any 
position with respect to the election of farmers nominees to the 
board 
wyatt said that batus based in louisville owns 696000 shares 
of farmers stock of which there were 68916614 shares 
outstanding as of oct 31 1987 
earlier this month a federal judge in nevada ordered farmers to 
place batus negotiation proposal in the proxy cards being sent to 
shareholders for the meeting 
the case was heard in nevada because farmers is incorporated 
there 
batus which owns a diversified group of businesses including 
retailers saks fifth avenue and marshall fields began the bidding 
in january with a 60 per share offer for farmers 
farmers is the nations thirdlargest home and auto insurer 
after state farm and allstate and the seventhlargest property and 
casualty insurer 
some analysts have said batus needs to raise its offer by 5 to 
20 a share if it expects to acquire farmers which has about 11 
billion in assets mostly in insurance 
the wall street journal reported monday that state insurance 
regulators and legislators had raised questions that could hinder 
the batus bid 
officials of the texas state board of insurance have questioned 
the companys ability to service the debt required to accomplish 
the deal 
in ohio the state house of representatives has approved a 
resolution expressing its concern about how the takeover might 
affect farmers policyholders and employees in that state 
a spokesman for batus british parent told the journal that it 
was responding to the questions from the texas authorities and 
believes it meets all the legal requirements to control insurance 
companies in texas and ohio 
before its purchase of farmers can be completed batus must get 
approval from insurance regulators in nine states regulators in 
several states including idaho illinois and kansas have asked 
the company for more information the journal said 
