the federal government chalked up a 239 billion deficit in its 
february spending after posting a rare budget surplus in january 
the treasury department reported monday 
meanwhile stock prices fell in the slowest trading of the year 
while the dollar followed suit and oil prices were mixed 
the treasurys latest monthly report on the governments 
spending and revenues followed a 161 billion surplus in january 
which had occurred because social security checks that month were 
mailed early and counted in the december spending figures 
so far this fiscal year the government has run up a fivemonth 
deficit of 897 billion 49 percent lower than the red ink 
incurred in the same period a year earlier 
the reagan administration is projecting a deficit of 1467 
billion for the fiscal year ending sept 30 down 24 percent from 
the 1504 billion deficit in 1987 
but many forecasters believe the small improvement will not be 
realized because they think the administration has used overly 
optimistic projections about the economy 
on wall street inflation fears and lingering postcrash anxiety 
sent stocks tumbling across the board with the dow jones average 
of 30 industrials dropping sharply at the opening and remaining 
down throughout the trading session 
