<TEXT>
campbell soup co is replacing the 
redandwhite labels on cooking soups used primarily as recipe 
ingredients but plans to keep the familiar 90yearold design on 
its eating soups the company said monday 
the new labels will feature color photographs of meals that can 
be made from recipes using campbells 16 varieties of cooking 
soups according to company spokesman kevin lowery 
the recipe for the pictured meal will be printed on the 
underside of the label along with another recipe and a cookbook 
offer 
the traditional redandwhite label was born in 1898 when a 
campbell executive was so inspired by the colors in cornell 
universitys new football team uniforms that he ordered the change 
from the previous orangeandblack label lowery said 
the redandwhite label went on to win the gold medallion for 
excellence at the 1900 paris exposition and was immortalized in pop 
art by the late andy warhol 
cooking soups such as chicken broth cream of mushroom and 
tomato constitute onethird of campbells market 
campbell initially will use the new labels on cans produced and 
sold in nine western states where the company will judge consumer 
reaction 
the company indicated the change the product of one years 
research could help consumers by saving shopping time and aiding 
menu planning 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

